    • Method Detail

      • apply

        public java.lang.Object apply(Action action)
        Description copied from interface: PreFunction
        Execute the pre-function and return the transientObject. The transientObject is saved by the workflow execution environment and is passed to the post function as it was returned by this method.

        Although this is a transient object that exists only during the execution of a workflow action it is supposed to implement the interface Object if the environment is a servlet container. This is because the pre function may be used to display a user screen to enter input and the post function may only be executed after the user screen was submitted. The two invocations of the methods in this case belong to different http hits. The transientObject may be stored in the servlet container session and if the environment is clustered the object may not travel from one node to the other.

        Specified by:
        apply in interface PreFunction
        Parameters:
        action - the action currently performed
        Returns:
        the transient object used later by the validator and the post-function
